The government of Zambia is set to restart the US $12m Pave Zambia road projects road projects on selected township gravel roads in Mushili, Ndeke, Itawa and Mackenzie townships of Bwana Mkubwa Constituency. Bwana Mkubwa Constituency Member of Parliament, Jonas Chanda confirmed the reports and said the Road Development Agency (RDA) working with local Zambian contractors FROG limited and VIRGIN SERVICES Limited will help in the construction of the roads. Also Read:Zimbabwe commence tarring of Karoi-Binga road  “With a good road network, farmers will be able get their produce to market. Moreover, we can’t further develop our tourism industry without improved roads and the much talked-about industrialization process cannot happen without having a good road network,” said the President.   